ON Tuesday, 4 January Makhadzi announced she will be hosting a one-woman show in Gaborone, Botswana. The event is set to take place on Saturday, 26 March. She will also be donating 10% of her profits to a charity organisation in Botswana. In a Facebook post, she wrote: “I have decided to do my own one woman show in Botswana, Gaborone. Date: 26 March. Venue: To be confirmed. Botswana are you ready? I will take 10% of my profits and donate it to a charity in Botswana. #iamafricanqueen.” Her friends and fans applauded her gesture. Jack Bohloko posted: “You will be the first South African to do that. You’re truly amazing Makhadzi... God will continue to elevate you.... SHINE.” While Mzamo Zondo commented: “I love you Makhadzi. South Africa is blessed to have such a wonderful woman who flies the South African flag to international countries. Go on and on. I’m proud of you and your success.” ALSO READ | UNATHI LEAVES SOCIAL MEDIA DROOLING But a handful of her supporters were not happy as they reminded her that charity begins at home. Vur Vi Speed said: “Why Botswana if I may ask because mo Limpopo gona le family tla go sokola tseo o ka di thusang with your charity? Makhadzi, we have been supporting you o sa fihla mo oleng now and batho ba Botswana bao tseba now and wena you choose them over us?” But in December last year, Makhadzi donated food parcels to 30 families for Christmas in Limpopo. At that time, she wrote: “I decided to release 30K to buy Christmas food parcels for 30 families. Mukondeni, Tshivhangani Mashama Village. Tuesday you will be getting food parcels for Christmas. I will be in Botswana, but I will send my team to give you food. Nama nanwaha riyaila rothe nga Christmas.”